Background Data on Hepatitis A Virus Infection in Argentina
-----------------------------------------------------------
[The following data on hepatitis A virus infection in Argentina have been
extracted fro the GIDEON Database by Dr. Steve Berger. - Mod.CP]
Evidence of prior disease is present in 95 percent of blood donors; 18.8
percent of children below age 13 years, and 45.5 percent over 14 years
(Buenos Aires). 55.0 percent of the general population are seropositive
(1996 to 1997).
Year / cases
1992 / 11 325
1993 / 14 482 (highest rates in Salta and Tucuman)
1994 / 28 488 (highest rates in San Juan)
1995 / 32 880
1996 / 29 727
1997 / 30 661
1998 / 25 782
1999 / 32 013
2000 / 40 245
2001 / 25 104
2002 / 19 279
Disease rates were 87.4 per 100 000 in 1994, and 100.8 per 100 000 in 1995.
In 1993, Buenos Aires Province reported rates of 30.9/100 000; 89.9/100 000
in 1996 (65.3/100 000 in Buenos Aires city).
--
Steve Berger
Geographic Medicine
Tel Aviv Medical Center
<Tel@post.tau.ac.il>
